latestPosts.caption:
As I inch closer to 26, I challenged myself to do 25 things that truly spark joy. First up? A dreamy solo beach day in Gokarna with a saree shoot I’d been visualising for months. But life threw a curveball — I got scammed, and the place I booked was in ruins. It was a lot to take in, but I reminded myself why I came. After a deep breath (and some non-negotiable skincare 😌), I walked 4–5 km, got my braids done, and found a peaceful beach spot that felt just right. I soaked in the view over breakfast, booked a same-day return, and turned the chaos into something beautiful. It didn’t go as planned — but sometimes, the mess makes the memory. Vlog drops today — can’t wait to show you how it all unfolded. 💛🌊

latestPosts.caption:
As I step closer to turning 26 this month, I gave myself a little challenge — to do 25 things that truly bring me joy. The first on my list was a solo beach day in Gokarna with a dreamy saree shoot I’d been visualising for so long. But the universe had other plans — I got scammed on day one, and the place I booked was completely destroyed. Honestly, it was overwhelming, but instead of giving up, I took a deep breath, did my skincare (because sunscreen is non-negotiable, no matter what 😌), walked 4–5 km, got my braids done, and finally found another spot by the beach that felt just right. Treated myself to a peaceful breakfast with a view, booked a same-day return, and made the most of it. Things didn’t go as planned, but sometimes, the mess becomes the memory.
